  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\set.theoretic.successor{n}]\nDefines: s := \\set.theoretic.union:of{n}:and{\\set.theoretic.singleton{n}} is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nwhen: n is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nDocumented:\n. called: \"successor of $n?$\"\n. written: \"n?^+\"\n. description: \"The successor $n^+ = n \\cup \\{n\\}$ of a natural number $n$. If $n$ has $n$ elements then $n^+$ has $n + 1$ elements, since $n^+$ adjoins $n$ itself as a new element. The same construction $x^+ = x \\cup \\{x\\}$ makes sense for any set.\"\nId: \"7fc5e8d2-efa4-4c81-8843-043e29947352\"",
